Another thing that's interesting is,

00:23:17.380 --> 00:23:20.760
what's the frame rate of a terminal?

00:23:21.440 --> 00:23:25.060
People think of it just scrolling text and printing out text,

00:23:25.090 --> 00:23:26.840
and you see it going by and you're like,

00:23:26.880 --> 00:23:29.840
yeah, well, that's kind of how the UIs must be.

00:23:30.000 --> 00:23:32.980
But you can actually push these things pretty far, right?

00:23:34.040 --> 00:23:34.880
You can.

00:23:36.500 --> 00:23:40.300
Interesting thing is I don't think anyone who sat down to develop a terminal

00:23:41.100 --> 00:23:44.640
was thinking in terms of frames per second.

00:23:46.200 --> 00:23:50.660
You know, they were just, they want to optimize the text output

00:23:50.980 --> 00:23:55.320
so that if you cut a large file, it didn't take forever to scroll through.

00:23:55.980 --> 00:23:57.740
- Right, or didn't flicker around or something.

00:23:58.260 --> 00:24:02.620
- Yeah, yeah, and later on people like myself and others

00:24:03.780 --> 00:24:06.220
were creating animations and things,

00:24:06.670 --> 00:24:09.220
and they're thinking, "Well, how fast can I push this?"

00:24:09.920 --> 00:24:11.220
And it turns out pretty fast,

00:24:12.150 --> 00:24:16.980
'cause terminals use your GPU to render the text,

00:24:18.399 --> 00:24:22.220
and if you send it text fast enough, it'll keep up, mostly.

00:24:22.900 --> 00:24:28.480
And I found that 60 frames a second is completely workable on most terminals.

00:24:31.080 --> 00:24:37.060
You don't really need that for most apps because if you're scrolling text,

00:24:37.120 --> 00:24:39.280
you can only move character at a time.

00:24:39.600 --> 00:24:42.960
It's not pixel perfect because it's kind of like a grid.

00:24:44.720 --> 00:24:47.240
So if you want to scroll at 60 frames a second,

00:24:47.320 --> 00:24:50.140
you'd have to move 60 lines in a second,

00:24:51.260 --> 00:24:53.320
Which text will just kind of whiz by.

00:24:53.680 --> 00:24:54.860
Yeah, it gets blurry anyway.

00:24:55.360 --> 00:25:01.820
